    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_589283713" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/589283713" />
    <a title="Jill Talley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7832039-jill-talley"><img alt="Jill Talley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1426547151p2/7832039.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/589283713?book_show_action=true">Feb 19, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jill Talley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jill Talley" href="/user/show/7832039-jill-talley">Jill Talley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7832039-jill-talley?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer589283713" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8879754226210180342">Going to give this a review, even though it already has many, because i would give it 4.5 stars if the &quot;halves&quot; were available.<br/><br/>I have a hard time finding any really good Fiction nowadays, let alone GREAT, and this is close to great. My only problems with it were: almost too brutal, and i can take a lot when i know it has to be there to make the book what it is. You know what you are getting into when you choose to read this type of book, but it HOVERED on being too much for me to take. Also - th</span>
  <span id="freeText8879754226210180342" style="display:none">Going to give this a review, even though it already has many, because i would give it 4.5 stars if the "halves" were available.<br /><br />I have a hard time finding any really good Fiction nowadays, let alone GREAT, and this is close to great. My only problems with it were: almost too brutal, and i can take a lot when i know it has to be there to make the book what it is. You know what you are getting into when you choose to read this type of book, but it HOVERED on being too much for me to take. Also - the suspense. Many people love suspense, I don't! I have to get there fast - to find out what happens! I can't take the waiting! I'm not a patient person.<br /><br />But my major complaint, and it still didn't stop me from really liking the book, was the relationship with the singer and the boy. I didn't find that it developed enough for ME - to feel like they got as close as the book had them out to be by the end. BUT, it still worked for me because the story was really good, good writing, a different book/story than i've read before, the end left me thinking and wishing for more of the book to read, and most of the character development was good. Also quite a few lessons were taught, in my opinion. I would highly recommend it.<br /><br />(One additional note: i had a few interruptions while reading it, so it took me a while to finish this one... for that reason, i went back and re-read the first chapter after finishing the book. Gave me a better feeling of the end, and the whole book even. Good stuff.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="8879754226210180342" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


